Implementing a [Content Security Policy (CSP)](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Content-Security-Policy) can significantly mitigate the threat of malicious users exploiting insufficient output encoding to achieve cross-site scripting (XSS) or code injection attacks when interacting with a language model system. For example, below is CSP restricts resources to approved origins. Allows certains assets and blocks unneeded scripts and frames. Locks down chatbot to only necessary assets.

```
Content-Security-Policy: 
  default-src 'self';
  script-src 'self' cdn.example.genai.com;
  style-src 'self' cdn.example.genai.com;
  img-src 'self' data: cdn.example.genai.com;
  font-src 'self';
  connect-src 'self' api.example.genai.com;
  frame-src 'none';
```
